        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">CCPA</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Policy_Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">CCPA Section 1798.120 requires businesses to provide consumers with the right to opt-out of the sale of personal information. Organizations must honor "Do Not Sell" requests and maintain records of opt-out status.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Legal_Citation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">CCPA Section 1798.120 - Right to Opt-Out of Sale of Personal Information</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation_Steps__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">1. Implement "Do Not Sell" opt-out mechanism on website and in Salesforce.
2. Track opt-out status in Contact/Lead records (CCPA_Do_Not_Sell__c field).
3. Process opt-out requests within 15 business days.
4. Maintain audit trail of all opt-out requests and status changes.
5. Train staff on CCPA opt-out procedures.</value>
    </values>
